article.headline: IUPUI 86, N. Dakota St. 74
article.story: INDIANAPOLIS -- Robert Glenn scored a game-high 33 points and Alex Young added 23 to lead IUPUI to an 86-74 victory against North Dakota State on Saturday night. Glenn added eight rebounds and made 15 of 16 free-throw attempts. Young had four 3-pointers for the Jaguars (7-2, 2-0 Summit League). Eric Carlson scored 20 points for North Dakota State (3-4, 1-1). An 18-5 run helped the Bison tie the score at 65-65 with 6:48 remaining, but Glenn took over, scoring the game's next seven points. Young hit a 3-pointer for a 75-67 lead with 4:12 to play, and Glenn hit 7 of 8 free throws down the stretch.
